o inspect resolved dependencies for the doxia-site-renderer. Using Maven POM transitive is essential here, but I wonder if the additional dependency, plexus-testing, is necessary for adequate coverage if I use @PlexusTest. The driver does insert deterministic entries before generation, but maybe adding maven-artifact and plexus-testing feels like overdoing it. The user suggests taking no action without concrete evidence. Upstream POM has plexus-testing, guice, and other dependencies that might not align with the generated scaffold's needs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing coverage requirements**\\n\\nFor meaningful coverage after adapting the API, I might need to add the Maven artifact testImplementation since public method signatures rely on org.apache.maven.artifact.Artifact, which Gradle might not include. If skin methods are avoided, then it won't be necessary. However, creating meaningful site renderer coverage should establish context for the skin and copy resources, which would require the Artifact class and a skin jar. I’m considering whether to recommend the maven-default-skin dependency and need to research its Maven coordinates version with site.vm.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jiXnPkHi8kDGrvxrFHrvt0K1|fc_074126066af60ccf016a3fb57a4a588195ba979500a2ddd296", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re, zipfile, io\n# list versions metadata\nurl='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/skins/maven-default-skin/maven-metadata.xml'\nxml=urllib.request.urlopen(url,timeout=20).read().decode()\nprint(xml[-2000:])\nversions=re.findall(r'<version>([^<]+)</version>', xml)\nfor v in versions[-5:]:\n try:\n  jar=urllib.request.urlopen(f'https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/skins/maven-default-skin/{v}/maven-default-skin-{v}.jar',timeout=20).read()\n  z=zipfile.ZipFile(io.BytesIO(jar))\n  entries=[n for n in z.namelist() if n.endswith('site.vm') or 'META-INF/maven' in n or 'cs